In his speech at the Congressional Hispanic Caucus Institute's 44th Annual Awards Gala, President Biden thanked the caucus members, his Cabinet, and the awardees for their contributions. He highlighted the accomplishments of his administration, such as job creation, reducing child poverty, expanding healthcare access, investing in infrastructure, and addressing climate change. He also discussed his efforts to reduce the cost of prescription drugs, support education, and promote small businesses. The President emphasized the need for gun control, defending voting rights, and comprehensive immigration reform. He concluded by expressing his optimism for the future of the United States and the importance of unity and diversity.